PROBLEM: 'For all integers '$n \geq 9,$' the value of\n'\[\frac{(n+2)!-(n+1)!}{n!}\]'is always which of the following?\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: \text{a multiple of 4}
[B]: \text{a multiple of 10}
[C]: \text{a prime number}
[D]: \text{a perfect square}
[E]: \text{a perfect cube}

PROBLEM: 'In unit square '$ABCD,$' the inscribed circle '$\omega$' intersects '$\overline{CD}$' at '$M,$' and '$\overline{AM}$' intersects '$\omega$' at a point '$P$' different from '$M.$' What is '$AP?$'\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: \frac{\sqrt5}{12}
[B]: \frac{\sqrt5}{10}
[C]: \frac{\sqrt5}{9}
[D]: \frac{\sqrt5}{8}
[E]: \frac{2\sqrt5}{15}

PROBLEM: 'Which of the following is the value of '$\sqrt{\log_2{6}+\log_3{6}}?$'\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: 1
[B]: \sqrt{\log_5{6}}
[C]: 2
[D]: \sqrt{\log_2{3}}+\sqrt{\log_3{2}}
[E]: \sqrt{\log_2{6}}+\sqrt{\log_3{6}}

PROBLEM: 'Two different cubes of the same size are to be painted, with the color of each face being chosen independently and at random to be either black or white. What is the probability that after they are painted, the cubes can be rotated to be identical in appearance?\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: \frac{9}{64}
[B]: \frac{289}{2048}
[C]:  \frac{73}{512}
[D]: \frac{147}{1024}
[E]: \frac{589}{4096}

PROBLEM: 'What is the maximum value of '$\frac{(2^t-3t)t}{4^t}$' for real values of '$t?$'\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: \frac{1}{16}
[B]: \frac{1}{15}
